# Google AI Services (Gemini / NotebookLM) Stream Rules List
# Updated: 2026-07-06
# Description: Routing rules for Google Gemini App and NotebookLM
# Source: Verified against Google's official firewall documentation
#   - https://support.google.com/a/answer/15627649 (Gemini App firewall settings)
#   - https://support.google.com/notebooklm (NotebookLM domain confirmed)
# Note: Google has not published a separate NotebookLM-specific host list.
#       NotebookLM runs on the same Gemini backend infrastructure, so the
#       shared Google AI hosts below should cover both. If matching is still
#       incomplete, packet capture is recommended (see note at bottom).

# ===== Primary App Domains =====
DOMAIN,gemini.google.com
DOMAIN,notebooklm.google.com

# ===== Shared Google AI / Backend Hosts (official, verified) =====
DOMAIN,www.google.com
DOMAIN,ogs.google.com
DOMAIN,apis.google.com
DOMAIN,www.googleapis.com
DOMAIN,jnn-pa.googleapis.com
DOMAIN,waa-pa.clients6.google.com
DOMAIN,ogads-pa.clients6.google.com
DOMAIN,optimizationguide-pa.googleapis.com
DOMAIN,streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com
DOMAIN,content-autofill.googleapis.com

# ===== Static Assets / CDN =====
DOMAIN,ssl.gstatic.com
DOMAIN,www.gstatic.com
DOMAIN,fonts.gstatic.com
DOMAIN,maps.gstatic.com
DOMAIN,encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com
DOMAIN,encrypted-tbn1.gstatic.com
DOMAIN,encrypted-tbn2.gstatic.com
DOMAIN,encrypted-tbn3.gstatic.com
DOMAIN,fonts.googleapis.com
DOMAIN,maps.googleapis.com

# ===== User Content / Images =====
DOMAIN,lh3.googleusercontent.com
DOMAIN,lh5.googleusercontent.com
DOMAIN,lh3.google.com

# ===== YouTube-related (used for embedded video results) =====
DOMAIN,i.ytimg.com
DOMAIN,yt3.ggpht.com
DOMAIN,www.youtube.com

# ===== Analytics / Ads (loaded by Gemini web UI) =====
DOMAIN,www.googletagmanager.com
DOMAIN,www.google-analytics.com
DOMAIN,static.doubleclick.net
DOMAIN,td.doubleclick.net
DOMAIN,googleads.g.doubleclick.net
DOMAIN,csp.withgoogle.com

# ===== Play Store (Android app install/update) =====
DOMAIN,play.google.com

# ---
# If domains above don't fully resolve matching issues, the Gemini/NotebookLM
# mobile apps likely also call additional internal Google API endpoints not
# publicly documented (e.g. specific *-pa.googleapis.com service shards).
# Recommend Surge Capture to identify any remaining Host entries.
